<!-- ===== PAGE: KNOW YOUR RIGHTS ===== -->
<div class="page" id="page-rights">
    <div class="kyr-layout" style="flex:1">
        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <aside class="kyr-sidebar">
            <div class="sidebar-label">Legal Categories</div>
            {{#sidebar_links}}
            <a class="sidebar-link {{active_class}}" onclick="scrollKYR('{{anchor_id}}',this)">{{sidebar_label}}</a>
            {{/sidebar_links}}
            <a class="sidebar-link" onclick="scrollKYR('statelaws',this)">State-wise Laws</a>
        </aside>

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <main class="kyr-main">
            <div class="kyr-search">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="color:var(--muted);font-size:20px">search</span>
                <input type="text" placeholder="Search for 'security deposit', 'eviction', 'RWA'..." id="kyr-search-input" oninput="filterKYR(this.value)" />
            </div>

            <!-- Legal Categories -->
            {{#legal_rights}}
            <section id="kyr-{{anchor_id}}" class="kyr-section">
                <div class="kyr-section-header">
                    <h2>{{category_title}}</h2>
                    <p>{{category_description}}</p>
                </div>
                {{#cards}}
                <div class="legal-card">
                    <h3>{{title}}</h3>
                    <p>{{body}}</p>
                    <div class="legal-tag">{{#source_url}}<span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size:14px">open_in_new</span> <a href="{{source_url}}" target="_blank" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:none">{{legal_ref}} <span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size:14px;vertical-align:middle">arrow_forward</span></a>{{/source_url}}{{^source_url}}<span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size:14px">gavel</span> {{legal_ref}}{{/source_url}}</div>
                </div>
                {{/cards}}
            </section>
            {{/legal_rights}}

            <!-- State-wise Laws Widget -->
            <section id="kyr-statelaws" class="kyr-section state-widget-section">
                <h2>State-wise Rent Laws</h2>
                <p>The Model Tenancy Act proposes states adopt standardized rental rules: security deposits capped at 2 months' rent (residential), mandatory written agreements registered with Rent Authority, 60-day eviction notice required, and a 3-tier dispute system (Rent Authority <span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size:14px;vertical-align:middle">arrow_forward</span> Rent Court <span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size:14px;vertical-align:middle">arrow_forward</span> Tribunal). Essential services cannot be disconnected during disputes. Rent revisions limited to 5-7% annually. Landlords cannot refuse renewal without valid grounds. States must notify adoption for these rules to apply locally.
                <br/>
                <a class="sw-link" href="https://prsindia.org/billtrack/the-model-tenancy-act-2021">Model Tenancy Act 2021 (PRS Analysis) <span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size:14px;vertical-align:middle">arrow_forward</span></a>
                </p>
                <div id="state-widget-kyr"></div>
            </section>
        </main>
    </div>
</div>
